{"_id":"NGyYLOAK1DdsnXFW","name":"The Brand of Greed","type":"gift","img":"icons/sundries/documents/document-sealed-red-yellow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","contentKey":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.the-brand-of-greed","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1,"folderName":"The City of Pigs"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>Bardolf Greed has granted you The Brand of Greed, a special pass that marks you as one of his trusted associates. This ornate document bears Bardolf's personal seal and signature, and it is recognized throughout Whitehaven as a symbol of ultimate authority. With The Brand, you get free access to any place in the city—factories, the slaughterhouse, the mine, even Greed's mansion—without anyone being able to object to your entrance. Guards, workers, and officials must comply immediately or face Bardolf's wrath. Additionally, you get 1 Additional Success when you exploit the Brand's importance and Bardolf's backing against any city dweller. Threaten them with Bardolf's displeasure, demand cooperation in his name, or leverage his resources—the Brand makes it clear you speak with his voice. However, carrying The Brand also marks you as an enemy to the Pig Heads and workers' rebellion. Arthur, Frank, and Clarence will see you as Bardolf's agent and tool of oppression.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - The City of Pigs","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The City of Pigs","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.the-brand-of-greed","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":1600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332114,"modifiedTime":1784280332114,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"Kr5YzWnvIv19IFM3","name":"The Meat of The God Under the Mine","type":"gift","img":"icons/consumables/meat/steak-raw-red.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","contentKey":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.the-meat-of-the-god-under-the-mine","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2,"folderName":"The City of Pigs"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You possess a piece of the divine flesh torn from The God Under the Mine. The meat regenerates slowly, allowing repeated use. Once per Scene, you can consume a portion of the flesh to temporarily gain supernatural power. When you do, immediately heal 1 Wound and gain 1 Additional Success on all physical actions you take for the rest of that Scene (attacks, climbing, running, lifting, swimming, etc.). The power courses through your body, making you stronger, faster, and more resilient. However, you must wait an entire Scene for the remaining flesh to regenerate before you can use this Gift again. **WARNING:** If you use this Gift in 2 consecutive Scenes without waiting for regeneration, the flesh is completely consumed and you permanently lose this Gift. The temptation to rely on divine power comes with a cost.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - The City of Pigs","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The City of Pigs","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.the-meat-of-the-god-under-the-mine","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":1700000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332115,"modifiedTime":1784280332115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"CDzXDL708mK9obaj","name":"There Is No House That Can Stop Me","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/air/wind-tornado-wall-blue.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","contentKey":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.there-is-no-house-that-can-stop-me","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3,"folderName":"The City of Pigs"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>**SPECIAL GIFT FOR GAROU THE OLD WOLF ONLY.** Those damned pigs get on your nerves and you can't stand them running away from your wrath. Your primal fury awakens when facing the Browne brothers, channeling the rage of the Big Bad Wolf who could blow down any house. You get 2 Additional Successes when you take action to destroy or overcome any environmental obstacle that stands between you and one of the three Browne brothers who has used their Gang Leader Gift (Arthur, Frank, or Clarence in mutated pig form). This includes: blowing down doors with supernatural breath, smashing through walls, demolishing barricades, collapsing tunnels to create shortcuts, breaking through floors or ceilings, destroying steam engines or machinery used as obstacles, or even collapsing entire buildings if they're hiding inside. Your rage makes the impossible possible—no structure can protect them from you. However, you hate to lose to them. If you have to leave or flee from a Scene without eliminating one of the three pig brothers, your shame and fury cause you to lose 1 Soma immediately. You are the Big Bad Wolf, and pigs cannot escape you.</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - The City of Pigs","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"The City of Pigs","source":"The City of Pigs","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.the-city-of-pigs.there-is-no-house-that-can-stop-me","scenario":"The City of Pigs","scenarioSlug":"the-city-of-pigs","sourceDirectory":"the-city-of-pigs","tags":[],"requirements":"","limitations":""},"sort":1800000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332115,"modifiedTime":1784280332115,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
